review_reply.reply_text: Thank you for your valuable feedback. My clinic is at the best interest to provide good treatment and documentation to the patients and we have done the same to you. My staff  provided you the online generated practo bill and the treatment summary with my seal and signature on it. Private clinics doesn't require GST. All my patients who have insurance got their reimbursement with the bill and documents, what I have provided and the insurance company doesn't ask for GST number for the treatment. I think you better check with your insurance company. Regarding service charge, it's the bank charging from us, we don't profit out of it and in our best interest we are trying to resolve that sooner.

survey_response.review_text: Visited the clinic for my father's dental health.The doctor is friendly and explains issues clearly. They also charge 1% service charge for debit cards and 2% for credit cards.
